          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-03-25T19:26:09Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Foreclosure Relief and Extension for Servicemembers Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Honoring America's Veterans and Caring for Camp Lejeune Families Act of 2012 to make permanent the extended one-year period after a servicemember's military service during which: (1) a court may stay proceedings to enforce an obligation on real or personal property owned by the servicemember prior to such military service; and (2) the sale, foreclosure, or seizure of such property is invalid without a court order or agreement. (The extended one-year period expired on December 31, 2014, and returned to a nine-month period under the Servicemembers Civil Relief Act.)</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-07-27T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
